⚙️ Basic Docker CLI Commands (Must Know 🔥)
🔹 1. Docker version check
docker --version
🔹 2. System info
docker info
📦 Image Commands
🔹 3. Image download (pull)
docker pull node
🔹 4. All images dekho
docker images
🔹 5. Image delete karo
docker rmi <image_id>
🟦 Container Commands
🔹 6. Container run karo
docker run hello-world

👉 First test command ✔

🔹 7. Running containers dekho
docker ps
🔹 8. Sab containers dekho (stopped bhi)
docker ps -a
🔹 9. Container stop karo
docker stop <container_id>
🔹 10. Container start karo
docker start <container_id>
🔹 11. Container delete karo
docker rm <container_id>
🔧 Advanced Useful Commands
🔹 12. Interactive container (terminal ke andar terminal 😄)
docker run -it ubuntu bash

👉 Isme tum container ke andar ka Linux use kar sakte ho

🔹 13. Port mapping (VERY IMPORTANT 🔥)
docker run -p 3000:3000 my-app
PS C:\Users\Administrator> docker stop web_server
web_server
PS C:\Users\Administrator> docker rm web_server
web_server
PS C:\Users\Administrator> docker run -d -p 8080:80 --name web_server httpd
d7c8fc7d31fae7c5d4b105b07e8f0e83e4c86bd8b7b9c0da458ff69a808370b5

👉 Format:

host_port : container_port
🔹 14. Container logs dekho
docker logs <container_id>
🔹 15. Container ke andar jao
docker exec -it <container_id> bash
🧹 Cleanup Commands
🔹 16. Sab stopped containers delete
docker container prune
🔹 17. Unused images delete
docker image prune
